## Example Output

### User Story

> **As a** team lead, **I want to** assign tasks to team members **so that I can** distribute work evenly and track who's responsible.

### Acceptance Criteria

**POSITIVE SCENARIOS**

**Scenario 1: Successfully assign task to team member**
- **GIVEN** I am a team lead with an unassigned task
- **WHEN** I select a team member and click "Assign"
- **THEN** the task shows the assignee's name and avatar
- **AND** the assignee receives a notification

**Scenario 2: Reassign task to different team member**
- **GIVEN** I have a task already assigned to Member A
- **WHEN** I change the assignment to Member B
- **THEN** Member B becomes the new assignee
- **AND** both members receive notifications

**Scenario 3: Assign task with due date**
- **GIVEN** I am assigning a task
- **WHEN** I set both an assignee and a due date
- **THEN** the task displays both the assignee and due date
- **AND** the assignee sees it in their "Upcoming" view

**NEGATIVE SCENARIOS**

**Scenario 4: Attempt to assign to deactivated user**
- **GIVEN** a team member has been deactivated
- **WHEN** I try to assign a task to them
- **THEN** I see an error "This user is no longer active"
- **AND** the task remains unassigned

**Scenario 5: Non-lead attempts to assign**
- **GIVEN** I am a regular team member (not a lead)
- **WHEN** I try to assign a task to someone else
- **THEN** the assign button is disabled
- **AND** I see a tooltip "Only team leads can assign tasks"

**Scenario 6: Assign to non-existent user**
- **GIVEN** I manually enter an email not in the system
- **WHEN** I try to assign
- **THEN** I see "User not found. Invite them first?"
- **AND** I'm offered an option to send an invite

**OUTLIER SCENARIOS**

**Scenario 7: Two leads assign same task simultaneously**
- **GIVEN** two team leads view the same unassigned task
- **WHEN** both click "Assign" at the same time
- **THEN** the first assignment wins
- **AND** the second lead sees "Task was just assigned to [name]"

**Scenario 8: Assign when at team member limit**
- **GIVEN** a team member has 50 active tasks (the limit)
- **WHEN** I try to assign another task to them
- **THEN** I see a warning "This person has reached their task limit"
- **AND** I can choose to proceed or select someone else

**Scenario 9: Assignment during system maintenance**
- **GIVEN** the notification service is temporarily unavailable
- **WHEN** I assign a task
- **THEN** the assignment succeeds
- **AND** I see "Notification will be sent when service resumes"

